at this involves not just the simple exchange of data, but also a complex pattern interference. The left hemisphere tends to process symbolic information sequentially, while the right specializes in gestalt and contextual awareness. I'm focusing on how these interact to produce coherent consciousness.\n\n\n**Expanding the Communication Lens**\n\nI'm now focusing on how the nature of the information flow between the hemispheres is not just structured symbols, but analog patterns. I'm exploring the implications of pre-symbolic communication, where the left side processes sequences and the right builds contextual awareness. It's a key framework, defining the information transfer process, and examining the interference of these two hemispheric outputs to generate coherent consciousness.\n\n\n**Probing Pre-Symbolic Realms**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the pre-symbolic communication, the raw exchange before structured meaning emerges. I'm exploring the implications of this analog pattern flow, where coherence is achieved through the interaction of left-hemisphere sequences and right-hemisphere contexts. This informs how PFC exhaustion impacts cognitive functions.\n\n\n"
